    <note>Liu(2) Congkai [28858] CHECK funerary inscription. Umehara's list indicates that nephews as well as sons were listed in funerary inscription, with both Qi(4) [28855] and Yu(16) [28857], listed in order as the #1 and #2 sones of Conglai's younger brother, Congyi(2) [28853]. In order, Ye(3) [28867], Du(5) [28868], Gou [28869], Lin(3) [28870] and Guo(4) [28871] are nephews and may all be sons of Congji [28860], but will be recorded as nephews of Congkai until the funerary inscription can be checked. Similarly, those names listed in Umehara as Congkai's grandsons will be treated, for the time being, as all great grandsons of Congkai's father. WDY, 3, p. 1848.</note>
